AB  - After recognizing the wide-spread use and importance of concepts of causality and causal laws, Feigl's definition of causality is discussed. Several research approaches employed in efforts to produce causal laws in economics are considered. A preferred approach is indicated and discussed. Its use in a famous economic study is described. In conclusion, it is suggested that further use of the preferred research approach will be very helpful in efforts to produce more causal laws in economics.
ER  - 

