AB  - The notion of causal ordering has been explicated for systems in the form of sets of linear algebraic equations and also for dynamic models consisting of linear differential equations. Since we often wish to aggregate or disaggregate models of systems or to consider the static equilibrium of a dynamic model, the question arises as to how these transformations from one model of a system to another affect the causal ordering of variables. The present paper provides some answers to this question.
ER  - 
